        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 8:19AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 819 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near North Johns to near Moundville. Movement
was east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Columbiana, Highway 145 and CR 46, American Village, Westover, Oak
Mountain State Park, Woodstock, Bibb County Airport, Camp Branch,
Hoover Veterans Park, Vandiver, Alabaster Veterans Park, Green Pond,
Maylene, Helena, Chelsea, Harmon, Randolph, Inverness, Brierfield
Ironworks Park, and Wilton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until noon CDT for
central, west central and east central Alabama.</instruction>
